    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"306601\">@Kyle Miller</span> Regarding <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/pull/5528\">lean4#5528</a>, Junyan just posted there the same confusion I had upon reading your comment:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Dot notation doesn't work when <code>x</code> is a function, so <code>(@x).f</code> isn't useful as an interpretation.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes, it does?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Logic</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Function</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Defs</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">β</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">β</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Injective</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 488652862,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1734015643
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(discussion thread for <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"113486\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/113486-announce/topic/v4.2E14.2E0.20and.20v4.2E15.2E0-rc1\">#announce &gt; v4.14.0 and v4.15.0-rc1</a>)</p>",
