    {
        "content": "<p>I agree with the sentiment of Kyle's point though. Implicit arguments are (almost) exclusively used for dependent arguments, and declarations in the <code>Function</code> namespace are almost exclusively used for nondependent functions, so the <code>(@x).foo</code> is rarely useful.</p>",
        "id": 488678634,
        "sender_full_name": "Floris van Doorn",
        "timestamp": 1734022628
    },
    {
